@node "Information" "Information"
 
 Here you may write your own notes about Packmaster.
@endnode

@node "Schlafen" "Sleep"

 With this you can send Packmaster to sleep. It is replaced by an AppIcon
 on the Workbench; double clicking the AppIcon reactivates Packmaster.
@endnode

@node "Hilfe" "Help"

 This menu item calls this help file.
@endnode

@node "Beenden" "Quit"

 This quits and closes Packmaster.
@endnode

@node "Packen" "Pack"

 With this you create an archive file (LHA, LHASFX, LZX, DMS, ZIP).
 When clicked a file requester appears. You select the path and enter the
 file name. These settings define the archive name and where to save it.
 Thereafter a path request appears. In this requester you select the files
 to pack.
 For packing DMS MSdos diskettes you select pc0 in drives listview.CrossDos
 must be installed to use this. LHASFX makes an LHA Run file. A Run File is
 a file that automatically decrunches and runs.
@endnode

@node "Entpacken" "Unpack"

 With this you decrunch an archive file. In @{"File" link "File" 0} select
 the archive to be decrunched. The decrunched dates written to the
 directory will be identical to the predefined outputpath as set in menu
 option @{"intern" link "Intern" 0}. The default is Ram:. To decrunch an MSdos DMS file select
 pc0 in drives listview. CrossDos must be installed to use this.
@endnode

@node "File einfügen" "Insert File into Archive"

 Here you select a file to be inserted into an existing archived file.
 In @{"File" link "File" 0} select the file to be added. A file requester
 will appear; select the file to be inserted.
@endnode

@node "File löschen" "Delete File from Archive"

 With this you can delete a file from an archive. In @{"File" link "File" 0} select the file
 to be deleted. A listview window will appear; the file you select will
 appear in the string gadget under the listview gadget. When you have
 finished selecting files click that gadget wider and the deletion will
 take place (after a security question has been answered).
@endnode

@node "Archiv löschen" "Delete Archive"

 With this you can delete an archive (after a security question has been
 answered).
@endnode

@node "Inhalt als File" "Content as file"

 With this you can the content of the archive file selected with @{"file" link "File" 0}
 write in a separat File.
@endnode

@node "Intern" "Internal"

 @{b}Font@{ub}       Here you can select a font for Packmaster.
 
 @{b}Output@{ub}     Here you can select where decrunched archives will be
            put

 @{b}AppIcon@{ub}    Here you can select the icon to be used when the menu
            item @{"sleep" link "Schlafen" 0} is selected.

 @{b}Text@{ub}       Here you can select the text reader to show these help
            pages. It must be Amigaguide compatible.

 @{b}Shell@{ub}      Here you can choose the size and position of the output
            window.

 @{b}PGP@{ub}        Here you can select the path of PGP.

 @{b}Source@{ub}     Here you select the directory in which your LHA-,LZX-,
            ZIP and DMS files can be found. The file request the
            with @{"File" link "File" 0} called is outclasses then on these drawer
            calibrated.


 @{b}Archive@{ub}    Here you select the directory into which your archives
            should be copied.

 @{b}ArcPath@{ub}    Here you can select the path of the packer.

 @{b}Recursiv@{ub}   Here can you select crunched with Path or not
@endnode

@node "Extern" "External"

 Menu item 0-4     Here you can register which
                   @{"external programs" link "Extern 0-5" 0} go into the
                   menu.

 Program   0-4     Here you can select the programmes.
@endnode

@node "Extern 0-5" "External 0-5"

 In this menu appear the titles of the @{"external" link "Extern" 0} progammes
 in menu items 0-4.
@endnode

@node "File" "File"

 Here you select the archive file to be used (LHA,LHASFX,LZX,DMS,ZIP). The
 selected file is used when the functions @{"Unpack" link "Entpacken" 0},@{"Insert File" link "File einfügen" 0},@{"Del File" link "File löschen" 0},
 @{"Testing" link "Test" 0},@{"Content" link "Inhalt" 0},@{"Unpack File out archive" link "File aus Archiv entpacken" 0} and @{"Content as file" link "Inhalt als File" 0} are called
@endnode

@node "Test" "Test"

 With this function an archive file selected with @{"file" link "File" 0}
 will be checked for errors.
@endnode

@node "Inhalt" "Content"

 Here you can see the content of the archive file selected with @{"file" link "File" 0}
@endnode

@node "Packer" "Packer"

 Here you select the packer programme (LHA,LHASFX,LZX,DMS,ZIP).
@endnode

@node "Diskpackoptionen" "Disk Pack Options"

 These placements be valied for the Diskpacker DMS.

 @{b}LO@{ub}             Beginblock, the block at which packing will start.

 @{b}HI@{ub}             Endblock, the block at which packing will finish.

 @{b}Mode@{ub}           Packmodus, the degree to which packing will be taken.

 @{b}Disk@{ub}           Whether a DD or a HD disk is to be packed.

 @{b}Drives@{ub}         The drive in which packing will occur.
@endnode

